# Decide the Brain SVX Rendering Model

## Unblocked 2026-07-12

The privacy grilling resolved (see the closed blocker ticket): tailnet is the
auth, single tier; the rendering model inherits a decided contract —
**secure mode by default** (PII spans masked), a floating **JoelClaw toolbar**
(left edge, feature flags) with session-scoped reveal, safe-at-rest data only
(reveal can never fetch beyond stored redacted excerpts), hard exclusions never
rendered. Toolbar + flag mechanics are THIS ticket's scope now. Optional:
general event streams to ClickHouse as system telemetry.

## Resolution (2026-07-12, grilled with Joel — "aligned")

1. **Supersession**: brain.joelclaw.com fully supersedes the joels-mac-studio
   `/notes/` viewer; retire at parity. One renderer, one URL scheme:
   `brain.joelclaw.com/<root>/<slug>` (namespace policy). Fleet doctrine:
   agents reference Brain notes by these URLs once pages 200 (exact-URL
   check stands); Studio mapping is the fallback until then.
2. **Components (AMENDED by Joel at close)**: building custom components and
   leveraging MDSvX/SvelteKit to its absolute fullest is a core project
   goal, not an edge case. Registered roots are trusted code sources —
   registration in `brain-roots.json` IS the consent boundary — so the wiki
   COMPILES repo-local `.brain/components/**` for real. The safety property
   survives as isolation, not refusal: a component that fails to compile
   errors loudly on its own page (visible error box, raw source folded
   under it) while the rest of the build proceeds — page-scoped failure,
   never whole-build-fatal. The pi-notes standard set ships wiki-side as
   the shared vocabulary; local components extend it freely; promotion into
   the standard set remains the path for cross-root reuse.
3. **Reference model**: build reads the registered local checkouts
   (`brain-roots.json` in dark-wizard is truth). A Brain page pins nothing —
   it renders current checkout state; provenance (root, path, commit) is on
   every page, so staleness is visible, never hidden. Editions remain the
   immutable layer.
4. **Sections/privacy**: no hand-maintained include-list. Default-render
   everything in registered roots EXCEPT the hard-excluded sections
   (captures, compaction-dumps, people, private-family-health) and any note
   with sensitive-flagged frontmatter (`privacy: sensitive`). Frontmatter
   wins over defaults.
5. **Daily practice**: automatic. The 6am pipeline pulls checkouts and
   rebuilds; retros/pages appear with zero curation — publishing to the
   paper IS writing Brain svx. The 2026-07-12 static retro page migrates to
   a rendered Brain page.
6. **JoelClaw toolbar v1**: fixed left rail; session-scoped flags
   (localStorage): secureMode default-ON masking marked spans in
   edition/source excerpts, reveal (auto-revert), provenance detail, graph
   panel toggle. Brain-note prose (Joel-authored) isn't masked; masking
   targets ingested third-party excerpts.

Items 3–6 resolved per recommendation under Joel's blanket "aligned" —
amendable. Spawns: build-brain-page-renderer (graph map),
build-joelclaw-toolbar (bugle map), retire-studio-viewer (task, blocked on
renderer parity).

## Grilling notes (2026-07-12, superseded by resolution)

- **Supersession (decided)**: brain.joelclaw.com fully supersedes the
  joels-mac-studio `/notes/` System Brain viewer; retire the old approach at
  parity. One renderer, one memorable URL scheme
  (`brain.joelclaw.com/<root>/<slug>`, per the namespace policy) usable from
  any device to explore the brain topology. FLEET DOCTRINE: when agents hand
  Joel a page/summary/reference to a Brain note, they use the resolved
  brain.joelclaw.com URL — to be documented fleet-wide (wiki-aware graft
  block + operator-network-context) at ticket close. Cutover honesty: agents
  mint these URLs only once pages render there (exact-URL 200-check rule
  stands); the Studio mapping remains the fallback until parity.

## Question

Joel's charter (2026-07-12, verbatim intent): the wiki should REFERENCE `.svx`
files across the Brain and render them in the SvelteKit app — not accumulate
hand-built static HTML pages. What is the rendering model?

Sub-questions to resolve in the grilling:

- **Reference, not copy**: does the wiki read `~/.brain` (and repo-local
  `.brain`s?) live at build time, or via a synced snapshot with provenance?
  Editions are immutable; Brain notes mutate — what does a page pin?
- **Which sections**: retros/resources/projects presumably yes; `sensitive`,
  captures, people, private-family-health are already excluded by AGENTS.md —
  is the include-list explicit or frontmatter-driven (`privacy:` key)?
- **Rendering**: mdsvex over Brain svx with the tufte tokens
  (`~/Code/joelhooks/tufte-mdsvx` as authoring guide); what happens to
  project-local components a note references?
- **Routes + linking**: `/brain/<section>/<slug>`? How do editions and the
  wikilink graph (`graph.json`, 704 nodes) cite Brain pages — does this
  supersede the System Brain URL mapping
  (`joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net/notes/...`)?
- **Daily practice**: session retros land as Brain svx (e.g.
  `resources/retros/three-things-theo-video-retro-2026-07-12.svx`) and the
  wiki picks them up — is that automatic on the 6am build, or curated?

Context: on 2026-07-12 a session retro was published as a hand-built static
page (`static/retros/2026-07-12-three-things-theo.html`, live on
daily.joelclaw.com) as a stopgap; Joel's reaction to that page is what chartered
this ticket. The static page migrates to the rendering model once decided.

Blocked by the privacy/publication boundaries ticket: rendering Brain notes
into the wiki is publication of Brain content, and sensitive-flagged pages must
not cross tiers until those boundaries are defined.
